title: Bike Watching in Boston
description: Visualizes bicycle traffic across Boston through an interactive map that highlights bike routes and station data. It features a time-filtering option, allowing users to view variations in bike traffic at different times of the day. This visualization tool aids urban planners, cyclists, and city officials in understanding traffic patterns and planning improvements to the bike network infrastructure.

title: Vehicle and Tire Recalls Analysis
description: Analyzed NHTSA vehicle recall data to identify trends in safety issues, applied machine learning models to predict recall initiatives with 99% accuracy, and evaluated manufacturer compliance using statistical analysis and data visualization.

title: Credit Card Fraud Analysis
description: Developed and deployed a credit card fraud detection model, leveraging data cleaning, feature engineering, and statistical modeling to enhance recall by 89% and improve fraud prediction efficiency.

title: 2022 League of Legends Match Data Analysis
description: Analyzed the 2022 League of Legends match dataset, exploring key performance metrics across regional leagues, and trained a RandomForestClassifier with optimized hyperparameters to predict match outcomes with 96% accuracy.
